1
00:00:00,767 --> 00:00:05,633
[DRAMATIC TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

2
00:00:05,767 --> 00:00:06,867
Damn you!

3
00:00:07,000 --> 00:00:08,533
Your suffering
is still not enough.

4
00:00:08,667 --> 00:00:10,600
You should suffer even more.

5
00:00:10,733 --> 00:00:13,667
Thea? Are you really
that insecure and desperate?

6
00:00:13,800 --> 00:00:15,600
- What?
- You wanted dad to fall!

7
00:00:15,733 --> 00:00:16,833
Your thinking is filthy!

8
00:00:16,967 --> 00:00:17,800
- [EXCLAIMS]
- Marj!

9
00:00:17,933 --> 00:00:19,300
Thea, stop it!

10
00:00:19,433 --> 00:00:20,800
Thea tried to hurt me.

11
00:00:20,933 --> 00:00:24,633
I give up. I'm done
playing games with you.

12
00:00:24,767 --> 00:00:26,033
Let's separate.

13
00:00:26,167 --> 00:00:27,700
This is not the end.

14
00:00:27,833 --> 00:00:29,133
I'm still a Torrecampo!

15
00:00:29,267 --> 00:00:31,800
Hey! You have no right
to anything here!

16
00:00:31,933 --> 00:00:33,700
If only I had told you

17
00:00:33,867 --> 00:00:36,267
what kind of person Thea was
from the very beginning,

18
00:00:36,400 --> 00:00:39,333
your life wouldn't have become
miserable with her

19
00:00:39,467 --> 00:00:41,667
I'm sorry about everything,
Edward.

20
00:00:41,800 --> 00:00:43,100
I forgive you, Dad.

21
00:00:45,700 --> 00:00:48,433
[DRAMATIC TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

22
00:00:51,500 --> 00:01:00,167
[DRAMATIC TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

23
00:01:04,667 --> 00:01:13,467
[DRAMATIC TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

24
00:01:15,800 --> 00:01:20,933
[DRAMATIC TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

25
00:01:32,667 --> 00:01:34,233
[SIGHS]

26
00:01:34,367 --> 00:01:36,000
- Marj?
- Yes?

27
00:01:36,133 --> 00:01:38,900
Please, could you get me
some water?

28
00:01:39,033 --> 00:01:40,033
I'm just thirsty.

29
00:01:40,200 --> 00:01:41,767
All right, Dad.

30
00:01:41,900 --> 00:01:42,867
Che!

31
00:01:43,900 --> 00:01:45,000
Weng!

32
00:01:46,867 --> 00:01:50,267
It seems like the people inside
the house can't hear me, Dad.

33
00:01:50,400 --> 00:01:51,467
I'll just get it myself.

34
00:01:51,600 --> 00:01:53,233
I'll be right back.

35
00:01:53,367 --> 00:01:54,500
Don't move, okay?

36
00:01:54,633 --> 00:01:55,600
[CHUCKLES]

37
00:02:03,933 --> 00:02:07,767
[FOREBODING MUSIC PLAYING]

38
00:02:11,867 --> 00:02:15,533
[FOREBODING MUSIC CONTINUES]

39
00:02:26,933 --> 00:02:28,500
<i> Damn you.</i>

40
00:02:28,633 --> 00:02:31,500
<i>You promised before
that you'd pay us 150 million</i>

41
00:02:31,633 --> 00:02:33,400
<i> if Ashley donated.</i>

42
00:02:33,533 --> 00:02:34,800
<i> Did you fulfill it?</i>

43
00:02:34,933 --> 00:02:36,933
<i> No.</i>

44
00:02:37,067 --> 00:02:40,533
<i>Of course, Paolo is really
your favorite.</i>

45
00:02:40,667 --> 00:02:42,767
<i>Their family matters more to you
than us.</i>

46
00:02:42,900 --> 00:02:45,900
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

47
00:02:58,333 --> 00:03:00,333
<i>Your suffering
is still not enough.</i>

48
00:03:00,467 --> 00:03:02,500
<i> You should suffer even more!</i>

49
00:03:07,533 --> 00:03:09,267
- Thea?
- Dad? Dad, are you okay?

50
00:03:09,400 --> 00:03:10,667
Thea!

51
00:03:10,800 --> 00:03:12,067
Oh, my god! Dad!

52
00:03:12,200 --> 00:03:13,733
What did you do?

53
00:03:13,867 --> 00:03:15,133
Marj, what is this?

54
00:03:15,267 --> 00:03:18,333
Why would you let dad
get near the pool?

55
00:03:18,467 --> 00:03:20,267
My God, Dad, are you okay?

56
00:03:20,400 --> 00:03:21,300
Don't touch me.

57
00:03:21,467 --> 00:03:23,167
Relax, you're now safe.

58
00:03:23,300 --> 00:03:24,333
I saved you.

59
00:03:24,467 --> 00:03:25,467
That's not true!

60
00:03:25,600 --> 00:03:27,667
I saw something else!

61
00:03:27,800 --> 00:03:29,467
What are you talking about?

62
00:03:29,600 --> 00:03:30,633
You know if I hadn't arrived,

63
00:03:30,767 --> 00:03:32,767
dad might have fallen
and drowned.

64
00:03:32,900 --> 00:03:34,133
And it's all your fault!

65
00:03:34,267 --> 00:03:36,133
Shouldn't you
have been watching him?

66
00:03:36,267 --> 00:03:38,000
I made sure
the wheelchair was locked

67
00:03:38,133 --> 00:03:39,467
before I left.

68
00:03:39,600 --> 00:03:40,733
You made sure?

69
00:03:40,867 --> 00:03:43,267
Then why is dad positioned here?

70
00:03:43,400 --> 00:03:44,967
Stop making excuses.

71
00:03:45,100 --> 00:03:47,267
You were showing off
but in the end,

72
00:03:47,400 --> 00:03:49,967
you almost killed dad
because of your negligence!

73
00:03:50,100 --> 00:03:52,433
What I don't understand
is why you're here?

74
00:03:52,567 --> 00:03:53,767
I just turned my back,

75
00:03:53,900 --> 00:03:56,300
and dad's wheelchair rolled?

76
00:03:56,467 --> 00:04:00,333
I was just passing by
and I saw dad in danger,

77
00:04:00,467 --> 00:04:02,333
so I ran and helped him.

78
00:04:02,467 --> 00:04:03,900
Liar.

79
00:04:04,033 --> 00:04:05,233
- I saw you.
- What?

80
00:04:05,367 --> 00:04:06,967
You brought me here.

81
00:04:08,000 --> 00:04:09,033
You're really evil!

82
00:04:09,167 --> 00:04:11,467
- [EXCLAIMS]
- Why did you do that?

83
00:04:11,600 --> 00:04:13,933
I don't know
what you're talking about!

84
00:04:14,067 --> 00:04:18,100
Maybe dad is still in shock
so he's not thinking straight.

85
00:04:18,233 --> 00:04:21,567
I'm the one who helped
yet I'm the bad one.

86
00:04:21,700 --> 00:04:25,033
Helped? What you mean is,
you were waiting for a chance

87
00:04:25,167 --> 00:04:27,500
for everyone to see
that I was negligent,

88
00:04:27,667 --> 00:04:29,867
so Edward and Paolo
would blame me.

89
00:04:30,000 --> 00:04:31,033
What do you really want?

90
00:04:31,167 --> 00:04:32,167
To separate us from dad?

91
00:04:32,300 --> 00:04:33,700
To kick us out of here?

92
00:04:33,833 --> 00:04:36,067
Are you really that insecure
and desperate?

93
00:04:36,200 --> 00:04:37,167
What?

94
00:04:37,300 --> 00:04:38,567
Marj, what are you talking
about?

95
00:04:38,700 --> 00:04:41,000
You're ridiculous.

96
00:04:41,133 --> 00:04:44,200
- Enough. Enough. Stop this...
- Admit it,

97
00:04:44,333 --> 00:04:47,100
you set all of this up because
you really wanted dad to fall!

98
00:04:47,233 --> 00:04:48,667
You're shameless!

99
00:04:48,800 --> 00:04:50,100
You're really accusing me?

100
00:04:50,233 --> 00:04:52,100
Your mind is filthy!

101
00:04:52,233 --> 00:04:54,233
Why don't you rinse
yourself off first?

102
00:04:54,367 --> 00:04:55,667
[SQUEALS]

103
00:04:56,400 --> 00:04:58,400
[WATER SPLASHING]

104
00:04:59,200 --> 00:05:00,500
Thea, stop that!

105
00:05:01,267 --> 00:05:03,733
[WATER SPLASHING]

106
00:05:03,867 --> 00:05:05,567
<i>- Marj!
- You're really provoking this!</i>

107
00:05:05,700 --> 00:05:06,800
You want chaos, don't you?

108
00:05:08,367 --> 00:05:09,933
Thea!

109
00:05:10,067 --> 00:05:11,333
Thea, stop it now!

110
00:05:11,467 --> 00:05:12,733
Leave me alone, Dad!

111
00:05:12,867 --> 00:05:14,800
I've been fed up with this woman
for a long time!

112
00:05:14,933 --> 00:05:17,133
- Enough!
- I'll shake your brain

113
00:05:17,267 --> 00:05:19,033
so you wake up to the truth!

114
00:05:19,167 --> 00:05:21,233
That i'll win more
compared to you!

115
00:05:21,367 --> 00:05:22,233
You animal!

116
00:05:22,367 --> 00:05:23,967
What the hell!

117
00:05:24,100 --> 00:05:26,833
Thea, stop it!
[CLAMORING]

118
00:05:26,967 --> 00:05:28,367
Marj!
[EXCLAIMS]

119
00:05:31,533 --> 00:05:32,667
Thea!

120
00:05:32,800 --> 00:05:34,700
[CLAMORING]

121
00:05:34,867 --> 00:05:36,967
You demon! Demon!

122
00:05:37,100 --> 00:05:38,200
You demon!

123
00:05:38,333 --> 00:05:40,833
[CLAMORING]

124
00:05:40,967 --> 00:05:42,033
Stop it, Thea!

125
00:05:43,200 --> 00:05:44,500
Marj!

126
00:05:44,633 --> 00:05:46,700
[CLAMORING]

127
00:05:49,600 --> 00:05:50,533
Thea, stop it!

128
00:05:50,667 --> 00:05:52,767
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

129
00:05:56,867 --> 00:05:58,133
What now?

130
00:05:58,267 --> 00:05:59,233
Thea!

131
00:06:03,200 --> 00:06:05,700
Paolo! Edward!

132
00:06:05,833 --> 00:06:07,533
Thea, stop it!

133
00:06:07,700 --> 00:06:08,600
Thea!

134
00:06:08,733 --> 00:06:09,933
Regina!

135
00:06:13,167 --> 00:06:14,133
Stop them!

136
00:06:16,400 --> 00:06:17,800
Thea!

137
00:06:17,933 --> 00:06:18,900
Marj!

138
00:06:19,033 --> 00:06:22,133
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

139
00:06:33,533 --> 00:06:34,600
Paolo!

140
00:06:36,000 --> 00:06:36,900
Marj!

141
00:06:37,033 --> 00:06:39,133
[INTENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

142
00:06:39,267 --> 00:06:40,633
<i> Let go of me!</i>

143
00:06:51,200 --> 00:06:52,533
[COUGHING]

144
00:06:57,767 --> 00:07:00,100
- [SPEAKS INDISTINCTLY]
- Thea, what are you doing?

145
00:07:00,233 --> 00:07:01,133
I think you've gone too far!

146
00:07:01,267 --> 00:07:03,933
Look! Marj almost died!

147
00:07:04,067 --> 00:07:06,367
That's not the only fault
of that woman!

148
00:07:06,500 --> 00:07:09,000
I saw earlier
that she wanted to hurt dad!

149
00:07:09,133 --> 00:07:10,267
Don't make things up!

150
00:07:10,400 --> 00:07:11,300
That's not true!

151
00:07:11,433 --> 00:07:12,733
You're lying!

152
00:07:12,867 --> 00:07:15,500
My own eyes saw that you wanted
to push dad's wheelchair

153
00:07:15,667 --> 00:07:17,433
- into the pool!
- That's not true!

154
00:07:17,567 --> 00:07:19,333
Marj is right!

155
00:07:19,467 --> 00:07:21,267
Thea tried to hurt me.

156
00:07:22,500 --> 00:07:23,867
Dad.

157
00:07:24,000 --> 00:07:26,867
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

158
00:07:34,433 --> 00:07:35,733
Are you okay?

159
00:07:38,267 --> 00:07:39,900
Let go of me!

160
00:07:40,033 --> 00:07:42,233
Why are you targeting me?

161
00:07:42,367 --> 00:07:44,767
I'm your spouse,
you should be siding with me!

162
00:07:44,900 --> 00:07:46,800
What? You're the one angry

163
00:07:46,933 --> 00:07:48,967
when you're the one
who committed the wrongdoing?

164
00:07:49,133 --> 00:07:50,133
Fine!

165
00:07:50,267 --> 00:07:52,400
You believe Marj again as usual!

166
00:07:52,533 --> 00:07:54,200
And then what,
I'm the bad one again?

167
00:07:54,333 --> 00:07:56,867
Dad himself confirmed
what Marj said.

168
00:07:57,000 --> 00:07:58,767
So stop denying it.

169
00:07:58,900 --> 00:08:00,400
Just tell the truth!

170
00:08:02,700 --> 00:08:03,867
Fine!

171
00:08:06,767 --> 00:08:08,833
I lost control!

172
00:08:08,967 --> 00:08:11,267
I snapped because of that
show off Marj!

173
00:08:12,400 --> 00:08:13,633
That's it?

174
00:08:14,567 --> 00:08:17,000
You almost hurt dad
and killed Marj

175
00:08:17,133 --> 00:08:18,833
over something so shallow?

176
00:08:20,100 --> 00:08:22,500
Edward, that's not shallow!

177
00:08:22,667 --> 00:08:24,300
Think about it!

178
00:08:24,433 --> 00:08:26,533
For all we know, Marj might
already be turning dad

179
00:08:26,667 --> 00:08:28,600
against us
so dad would hate you

180
00:08:28,733 --> 00:08:32,267
even though
you're his real child!

181
00:08:32,400 --> 00:08:34,933
I only did that because I wanted
to secure our future

182
00:08:35,067 --> 00:08:35,967
in this house!

183
00:08:36,100 --> 00:08:37,733
Is that all that matters to you?

184
00:08:38,767 --> 00:08:40,900
Being clean in dad's eyes?

185
00:08:41,033 --> 00:08:43,367
Making sure we inherit a lot?

186
00:08:43,500 --> 00:08:46,233
That you don't care
even if you hurt other people?

187
00:08:46,367 --> 00:08:49,167
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

188
00:08:51,367 --> 00:08:52,433
[SIGHS]

189
00:08:54,133 --> 00:08:55,600
I thought I lost you, Love.

190
00:08:56,767 --> 00:08:57,867
I didn't know what to do

191
00:08:58,000 --> 00:08:59,633
if something bad happened
to you.

192
00:09:00,667 --> 00:09:02,667
I was so scared earlier.

193
00:09:04,633 --> 00:09:05,967
I'm okay now.

194
00:09:07,033 --> 00:09:08,767
Good thing you came.

195
00:09:09,933 --> 00:09:11,667
Thank you for saving my life.

196
00:09:11,800 --> 00:09:12,900
[CHUCKLES]

197
00:09:13,033 --> 00:09:16,300
I guess, old habits die hard.

198
00:09:17,267 --> 00:09:18,967
Nothing has changed.

199
00:09:20,033 --> 00:09:22,533
I still attract trouble and...

200
00:09:24,533 --> 00:09:26,467
you're still there to rescue me.

201
00:09:31,533 --> 00:09:35,733
And to be honest,
I miss being your hero.

202
00:09:38,600 --> 00:09:41,533
Marj, I miss us...

203
00:09:42,733 --> 00:09:43,700
so much.

204
00:09:43,833 --> 00:09:48,100
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

205
00:10:01,500 --> 00:10:02,867
So what do you want?

206
00:10:03,700 --> 00:10:05,800
Should I just sit
on the sidelines

207
00:10:05,933 --> 00:10:08,733
and watch them take everything
from us?

208
00:10:10,567 --> 00:10:12,667
- I'm doing...
- Enough!

209
00:10:13,567 --> 00:10:16,667
Don't use Ashley and me
as your excuse

210
00:10:16,800 --> 00:10:18,933
for all the wrong decisions
you're making.

211
00:10:20,000 --> 00:10:21,100
Wow!

212
00:10:21,933 --> 00:10:23,833
You're amazing!

213
00:10:23,967 --> 00:10:28,000
The way you talk, it's like
I never did anything right.

214
00:10:28,133 --> 00:10:30,600
Maybe you're forgetting, Edward,

215
00:10:30,733 --> 00:10:33,033
I was the one who saved you.

216
00:10:34,700 --> 00:10:37,833
I stayed by your side

217
00:10:37,967 --> 00:10:40,067
during the times
when they pushed you away

218
00:10:40,200 --> 00:10:41,600
and didn't want you!

219
00:10:42,867 --> 00:10:47,167
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

220
00:10:51,933 --> 00:10:52,933
What?

221
00:10:53,633 --> 00:10:55,333
You have nothing to say now?

222
00:10:57,233 --> 00:10:58,333
I tried.

223
00:11:00,533 --> 00:11:01,667
I tried, Thea.

224
00:11:04,467 --> 00:11:06,267
I tried to understand you.

225
00:11:08,500 --> 00:11:11,533
I forgave you for deceiving me,

226
00:11:11,667 --> 00:11:15,000
for lying to me about Ashley.

227
00:11:16,100 --> 00:11:17,233
I stayed.

228
00:11:18,633 --> 00:11:21,900
Because I believed,
somewhere in there...

229
00:11:23,567 --> 00:11:25,067
you loved me too.

230
00:11:26,933 --> 00:11:30,200
That this family
is worth saving.

231
00:11:31,333 --> 00:11:32,500
Edward...

232
00:11:33,567 --> 00:11:36,233
I did love you, Edward,
and you know that.

233
00:11:36,367 --> 00:11:37,967
No, you don't love me.

234
00:11:40,800 --> 00:11:43,300
What you love
is the surname I carry.

235
00:11:44,600 --> 00:11:47,233
What matters to you
is the wealth,

236
00:11:47,367 --> 00:11:53,667
the status you thought we'd get
because I'm the real Torrecampo.

237
00:11:53,800 --> 00:11:55,733
- [STAMMERRS]
- You...

238
00:11:55,867 --> 00:11:57,667
You're not after life with me.

239
00:11:59,500 --> 00:12:01,967
You're just after my money.

240
00:12:02,100 --> 00:12:03,800
No.

241
00:12:03,933 --> 00:12:06,167
- That's not true.
- That is the truth!

242
00:12:07,333 --> 00:12:11,033
And that's the most painful
realization of all.

243
00:12:12,833 --> 00:12:16,067
I'm tired of dealing with
someone who will do anything,

244
00:12:16,233 --> 00:12:21,367
even evil, for ambition,
for money.

245
00:12:23,000 --> 00:12:24,967
I'm done, Thea.

246
00:12:25,100 --> 00:12:29,233
I give up, I'm done playing
games with you.

247
00:12:29,367 --> 00:12:31,800
What are you saying?
[STAMMERS]

248
00:12:31,933 --> 00:12:33,533
Let's end this.

249
00:12:35,233 --> 00:12:36,967
Let's separate.

250
00:12:37,100 --> 00:12:40,433
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

251
00:12:43,600 --> 00:12:45,200
Are you serious, Edward?

252
00:12:47,633 --> 00:12:50,467
If I wasn't here, what do you
think would happen to you?

253
00:12:51,567 --> 00:12:53,933
What, you'll go back
to being a loser?

254
00:12:55,533 --> 00:12:57,267
Because let's face it,

255
00:12:57,567 --> 00:12:59,767
without me,

256
00:12:59,900 --> 00:13:03,033
you would have been swallowed
by this family a long time ago.

257
00:13:03,167 --> 00:13:05,367
Maybe you're forgetting, Edward,

258
00:13:08,467 --> 00:13:12,567
I was the one
who gave you a spine.

259
00:13:15,733 --> 00:13:21,167
I was your voice when they
treated you like trash!

260
00:13:23,033 --> 00:13:26,267
So without me,
you're just a shadow.

261
00:13:28,100 --> 00:13:31,300
A shadow behind Paolo
with no direction.

262
00:13:31,433 --> 00:13:32,667
That's it.

263
00:13:32,800 --> 00:13:36,200
Right there.
That's where you're good.

264
00:13:36,333 --> 00:13:38,867
That's where you're good at,
insulting me.

265
00:13:40,000 --> 00:13:43,300
That's exactly the reason
why I never got anywhere.

266
00:13:44,667 --> 00:13:46,500
Because you kept drilling
into my head

267
00:13:46,633 --> 00:13:48,400
that I was worthless.

268
00:13:48,533 --> 00:13:49,467
That I was a loser.

269
00:13:49,600 --> 00:13:52,067
But the truth is,

270
00:13:52,200 --> 00:13:54,567
you were the one
dragging me down.

271
00:13:58,700 --> 00:14:00,167
That's why, Thea...

272
00:14:03,033 --> 00:14:04,333
I'm letting you go.

273
00:14:05,967 --> 00:14:08,100
I'm letting you go now.

274
00:14:08,233 --> 00:14:09,967
- No.
- I should have done this...

275
00:14:11,000 --> 00:14:12,367
a very long time ago.

276
00:14:17,500 --> 00:14:20,100
Mommy, Miss Weng told us
what happened.

277
00:14:20,233 --> 00:14:22,100
Are you all right?
Did you get hurt?

278
00:14:22,600 --> 00:14:23,933
Sweetie, I'm okay.

279
00:14:24,067 --> 00:14:25,100
I'm okay now.

280
00:14:25,833 --> 00:14:28,433
I'm sure mom was the one
who started this again.

281
00:14:29,400 --> 00:14:32,733
I'm really sorry,
Auntie Marj, Uncle Paolo.

282
00:14:32,867 --> 00:14:35,300
Ashley, don't apologize.

283
00:14:35,433 --> 00:14:37,800
You have nothing to do
with what your mom did.

284
00:14:39,000 --> 00:14:39,933
She's right.

285
00:14:40,067 --> 00:14:41,167
It's not your responsibility
to answer

286
00:14:41,300 --> 00:14:42,800
for your mom's actions.

287
00:14:46,533 --> 00:14:48,800
I'm glad you're not angry
with me.

288
00:14:49,933 --> 00:14:51,033
What?

289
00:14:51,367 --> 00:14:54,000
Sweetie, never would I be angry
at you.

290
00:14:54,133 --> 00:14:56,667
In fact, I owe you a lot.

291
00:14:56,800 --> 00:14:58,667
Because if not for you,

292
00:14:58,800 --> 00:15:00,700
Jasmine might not be here
anymore.

293
00:15:02,700 --> 00:15:05,500
We are extremely grateful
to you, my child.

294
00:15:05,933 --> 00:15:07,733
And we love you very much.

295
00:15:09,233 --> 00:15:12,233
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

296
00:15:26,833 --> 00:15:27,733
Fine!

297
00:15:28,900 --> 00:15:30,367
All right!

298
00:15:30,500 --> 00:15:32,567
Let's separate.

299
00:15:32,700 --> 00:15:34,467
But remember this.

300
00:15:36,067 --> 00:15:40,067
I will never give Ashley to you.

301
00:15:40,200 --> 00:15:43,100
I will not leave this house
without her!

302
00:15:43,233 --> 00:15:44,467
Ashley is 15.

303
00:15:46,000 --> 00:15:47,767
You can't force her

304
00:15:47,900 --> 00:15:49,833
because she has the right
to choose

305
00:15:49,967 --> 00:15:51,233
who she wants to go with.

306
00:15:51,367 --> 00:15:53,000
She can't stay with you

307
00:15:53,133 --> 00:15:54,700
because she's not
your real child.

308
00:15:54,833 --> 00:15:58,000
In the eyes of the law,
I am still her father!

309
00:15:59,400 --> 00:16:00,833
And between the two of us,

310
00:16:01,167 --> 00:16:03,433
I can provide her
with a better life!

311
00:16:05,600 --> 00:16:09,733
Do you really think
after all the lies,

312
00:16:10,033 --> 00:16:11,900
deception, and manipulation
you did...

313
00:16:13,500 --> 00:16:15,500
you think she would still
choose you?

314
00:16:18,567 --> 00:16:20,367
Think about it.

315
00:16:21,633 --> 00:16:24,833
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

316
00:16:31,100 --> 00:16:33,833
[SOBBING]

317
00:16:41,200 --> 00:16:44,767
[INTENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

318
00:16:52,667 --> 00:16:53,867
<i> Ashley?</i>

319
00:16:56,333 --> 00:16:57,167
- Ashley.
- Mom.

320
00:16:57,300 --> 00:16:58,667
We're leaving this house now.

321
00:16:58,800 --> 00:17:00,500
We're leaving
your worthless father.

322
00:17:00,633 --> 00:17:02,100
Mom, I don't want to leave.

323
00:17:02,233 --> 00:17:03,933
I want to stay with dad.

324
00:17:04,067 --> 00:17:05,500
Stop it! I'm your mother!

325
00:17:05,633 --> 00:17:06,767
So you should come with me.

326
00:17:06,900 --> 00:17:08,433
- Mom!
- Wait! You heard the child.

327
00:17:08,567 --> 00:17:10,200
She doesn't want to leave, Thea.

328
00:17:10,333 --> 00:17:11,500
Don't interfere.

329
00:17:11,633 --> 00:17:14,267
She's my child
so I should be obeyed not her!

330
00:17:14,400 --> 00:17:15,367
- Get out of there!
- Mom, please.

331
00:17:15,533 --> 00:17:17,400
- I don't want to leave!
- Move!

332
00:17:17,533 --> 00:17:19,767
I want to stay.

333
00:17:19,900 --> 00:17:23,567
So if you love me,
please, just let me be, Mom.

334
00:17:23,700 --> 00:17:25,167
You're ungrateful!

335
00:17:25,833 --> 00:17:28,500
After everything I did
for you...

336
00:17:29,733 --> 00:17:31,200
this is what you do to me?

337
00:17:31,333 --> 00:17:34,100
You'll just leave me hanging?

338
00:17:34,367 --> 00:17:35,500
No! You're coming with me!

339
00:17:35,633 --> 00:17:37,033
Mom, I don't want to!

340
00:17:37,167 --> 00:17:38,033
No!

341
00:17:38,167 --> 00:17:40,433
Ashley already made her choice!

342
00:17:40,567 --> 00:17:42,933
Don't force what you want.

343
00:17:43,067 --> 00:17:46,967
If you try to force her,
you'll have to face me.

344
00:17:47,100 --> 00:17:50,667
From now on, you are not welcome
in this house.

345
00:17:50,833 --> 00:17:54,767
So, I want you to leave.

346
00:17:55,800 --> 00:17:56,867
Now!

347
00:18:00,433 --> 00:18:01,533
Edward, please.

348
00:18:01,667 --> 00:18:03,767
Please don't do this to me,
please.

349
00:18:05,400 --> 00:18:06,900
Let me make it up to you.

350
00:18:07,033 --> 00:18:08,967
I know I made many mistakes

351
00:18:09,100 --> 00:18:10,567
but let me make it up to you.

352
00:18:10,700 --> 00:18:14,267
I can prove that I can still be
a good person. Please.

353
00:18:14,400 --> 00:18:15,533
Too late for that.

354
00:18:16,500 --> 00:18:18,600
I've given you so many chances.

355
00:18:18,733 --> 00:18:20,633
But you disappointed me
again and again.

356
00:18:20,767 --> 00:18:22,067
- No.
- It would have been fine

357
00:18:22,233 --> 00:18:23,767
if you only hurt me.

358
00:18:23,900 --> 00:18:25,567
But to drag other people
into it?

359
00:18:25,700 --> 00:18:29,567
Even dad, who is weak and sick,
and unable to defend himself,

360
00:18:29,700 --> 00:18:31,133
you're going to dragged him
into this too?

361
00:18:32,300 --> 00:18:33,567
Oh, come on!

362
00:18:33,700 --> 00:18:34,700
Admit it!

363
00:18:34,833 --> 00:18:36,800
You've long wanted
to do that to your father.

364
00:18:36,933 --> 00:18:39,567
But you couldn't do it
because you're weak.

365
00:18:39,700 --> 00:18:41,567
So I finish the job for you!

366
00:18:41,700 --> 00:18:42,700
No, Thea!

367
00:18:43,867 --> 00:18:46,933
Even if I'm angry at dad,
I would never do what you did!

368
00:18:48,267 --> 00:18:50,833
Because he's still my father
and I love him!

369
00:18:56,467 --> 00:18:57,633
Thea.

370
00:19:01,833 --> 00:19:04,233
Get out of my house!

371
00:19:05,600 --> 00:19:07,800
Dad, please.

372
00:19:09,833 --> 00:19:11,467
Dad, please.

373
00:19:12,833 --> 00:19:14,267
You heard dad, didn't you?

374
00:19:14,400 --> 00:19:15,333
Leave now!

375
00:19:15,467 --> 00:19:17,667
[SOBBING]

376
00:19:17,800 --> 00:19:18,567
No.

377
00:19:19,033 --> 00:19:20,433
Ashley.

378
00:19:20,567 --> 00:19:21,667
Ashley, my child.

379
00:19:22,767 --> 00:19:24,233
Ashley, come with me.

380
00:19:25,100 --> 00:19:27,200
Come with me.

381
00:19:27,333 --> 00:19:29,200
Please, my child.

382
00:19:29,367 --> 00:19:32,733
I think it's best
for you to leave, Mom.

383
00:19:32,867 --> 00:19:37,033
[SOBBING]

384
00:19:40,533 --> 00:19:42,133
[GRUMBLES]

385
00:19:42,267 --> 00:19:43,433
Fine!

386
00:19:45,733 --> 00:19:47,000
I'll leave!

387
00:19:48,633 --> 00:19:50,967
But this is not the end.

388
00:19:51,100 --> 00:19:53,133
Do you understand?

389
00:19:53,267 --> 00:19:57,033
I'm still a Torrecampo
and I have rights to this house!

390
00:19:57,167 --> 00:20:00,167
Hey, you have no right
to anything here!

391
00:20:00,300 --> 00:20:02,700
Everything you see here
belongs to my parents!

392
00:20:03,933 --> 00:20:05,233
Really?

393
00:20:07,300 --> 00:20:09,400
This. This.

394
00:20:09,533 --> 00:20:12,400
This vase is mine.

395
00:20:12,533 --> 00:20:16,433
This was given to me by my
client so I'm taking this home!

396
00:20:16,567 --> 00:20:19,067
This painting is mine too.

397
00:20:19,200 --> 00:20:22,867
I took this from my old house
and I'm taking it home too!

398
00:20:24,167 --> 00:20:27,400
What are you still doing?
Open the door now!

399
00:20:27,533 --> 00:20:29,567
You animals!

400
00:20:29,700 --> 00:20:32,500
[SOBBING]

401
00:20:36,933 --> 00:20:40,700
[SOBBING]

402
00:20:40,833 --> 00:20:44,933
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

403
00:20:50,100 --> 00:20:51,500
[GRUMBLES]

404
00:20:51,633 --> 00:20:52,533
To hell with them!

405
00:20:52,667 --> 00:20:53,667
What do they think?

406
00:20:53,800 --> 00:20:56,333
I'll kneel and beg them?

407
00:20:56,467 --> 00:20:57,667
In their dreams!

408
00:20:57,800 --> 00:20:59,400
I can survive on my own.

409
00:20:59,533 --> 00:21:00,867
I don't need them!

410
00:21:01,000 --> 00:21:02,100
Damn it!

411
00:21:02,233 --> 00:21:04,300
[LINE RINGING]

412
00:21:04,433 --> 00:21:07,367
Girl, are you still in Vietnam?

413
00:21:07,500 --> 00:21:09,533
Can I crash at your place
for now?

414
00:21:09,700 --> 00:21:11,100
I'm not back in Manila
until next week.

415
00:21:11,233 --> 00:21:14,433
Wait a second,
why do you sound like that?

416
00:21:14,567 --> 00:21:16,133
<i> Are you okay?</i>

417
00:21:16,267 --> 00:21:17,633
Never mind.

418
00:21:17,767 --> 00:21:19,200
Forget that I asked.

419
00:21:20,867 --> 00:21:24,667
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

420
00:21:32,867 --> 00:21:35,200
Should I not have done that?

421
00:21:37,100 --> 00:21:40,800
I didn't want mom to leave,
but...

422
00:21:40,933 --> 00:21:42,833
Don't worry, Ash.

423
00:21:43,000 --> 00:21:44,833
It's really hard to adjust
at first

424
00:21:44,967 --> 00:21:48,267
but I'm sure you'll see
Auntie Thea again.

425
00:21:49,633 --> 00:21:51,100
Your dad is right, Ash.

426
00:21:51,233 --> 00:21:53,267
I think it's better
that you stay here

427
00:21:53,400 --> 00:21:55,167
so he has company

428
00:21:55,300 --> 00:21:56,867
and so you'll be better
taken care of.

429
00:21:59,667 --> 00:22:01,800
I know that, Auntie.

430
00:22:03,067 --> 00:22:07,600
It's just that I'm going
to miss my mom.

431
00:22:08,733 --> 00:22:11,000
Mommy can be your mom

432
00:22:11,133 --> 00:22:12,833
while Auntie Thea isn't here.

433
00:22:14,333 --> 00:22:16,367
I mean, we're sisters.

434
00:22:17,233 --> 00:22:18,600
Dad is also your father.

435
00:22:19,133 --> 00:22:20,933
So mom can be your mom, too.

436
00:22:23,433 --> 00:22:24,167
Right, Mommy?

437
00:22:26,467 --> 00:22:28,033
Of course.

438
00:22:28,567 --> 00:22:31,833
But I know I can't replace
your mom.

439
00:22:31,967 --> 00:22:34,567
But I promise you,
I'll always be here for you

440
00:22:34,700 --> 00:22:36,567
anytime you need me.

441
00:22:37,300 --> 00:22:39,233
I'll take care of you.

442
00:22:39,367 --> 00:22:42,600
Your dad, Paolo, and I
will take care of you.

443
00:22:46,433 --> 00:22:48,067
Thank you.

444
00:22:48,200 --> 00:22:50,567
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

445
00:22:58,533 --> 00:23:01,867
[DRAMATIC MUSIC CONTINUES]

446
00:23:14,433 --> 00:23:16,767
<i> I should be...</i>

447
00:23:16,900 --> 00:23:19,100
<i>the one blamed for everything
that happened here.</i>

448
00:23:21,900 --> 00:23:23,067
If only...

449
00:23:24,867 --> 00:23:26,267
I had told you...

450
00:23:27,733 --> 00:23:29,200
what kind of person
Thea really was

451
00:23:29,333 --> 00:23:30,533
from the very beginning...

452
00:23:33,567 --> 00:23:35,233
this wouldn't have happened.

453
00:23:36,700 --> 00:23:38,833
You wouldn't have married her.

454
00:23:39,167 --> 00:23:42,533
Your life wouldn't have become
miserable with her.

455
00:23:44,267 --> 00:23:45,433
My child...

456
00:23:48,667 --> 00:23:50,333
I greatly admire you...

457
00:23:51,400 --> 00:23:57,100
because you endured Thea
all these years.

458
00:23:57,267 --> 00:24:00,367
But you shouldn't regret
letting her go.

459
00:24:00,500 --> 00:24:02,033
She doesn't deserve you.

460
00:24:03,900 --> 00:24:06,133
Just like me,

461
00:24:06,267 --> 00:24:07,867
I don't deserve you.

462
00:24:11,167 --> 00:24:13,533
I'm sorry about everything,
Edward.

463
00:24:22,300 --> 00:24:24,300
I am...

464
00:24:27,900 --> 00:24:30,133
I'm terribly sorry, my son.

465
00:24:32,300 --> 00:24:33,367
Dad.

466
00:24:37,733 --> 00:24:38,567
[SOBBING]

467
00:24:39,633 --> 00:24:49,600
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

468
00:24:51,700 --> 00:24:53,800
[SOBBING]

469
00:24:57,433 --> 00:25:00,133
[SOBBING]

470
00:25:00,267 --> 00:25:01,367
Dad.

471
00:25:02,500 --> 00:25:04,567
Yes, I forgive you.

472
00:25:04,700 --> 00:25:06,100
I forgive you, Dad.

473
00:25:10,167 --> 00:25:11,233
Thank you.

474
00:25:11,367 --> 00:25:12,767
["KATOTOHANAN"
BY JESSICA VILLARUBIN PLAYING]

475
00:25:12,900 --> 00:25:14,800
Thank you for forgiving me.

476
00:25:16,800 --> 00:25:19,400
Thank you for accepting me back
as your father.

477
00:25:22,133 --> 00:25:24,700
Despite everything I did to you.

478
00:25:32,033 --> 00:25:35,567
Even when you made the mistake
of pushing me toward Thea...

479
00:25:37,733 --> 00:25:40,600
that mistake brought me
to the best thing

480
00:25:40,733 --> 00:25:42,433
that happened in my life.

481
00:25:43,933 --> 00:25:45,133
Ashley.

482
00:25:47,533 --> 00:25:49,533
Even if my marriage failed, Dad,

483
00:25:49,667 --> 00:25:51,900
I won't let our family fail.

484
00:25:54,233 --> 00:25:55,800
I'll rebuild us.

485
00:25:56,967 --> 00:25:58,167
I promise, Dad.

486
00:25:58,300 --> 00:26:05,200
["KATOTOHANAN" THEME MUSIC
PLAYING]

487
00:26:22,100 --> 00:26:23,367
What are you doing here, Thea?

488
00:26:23,500 --> 00:26:26,600
Do you regret letting me go?

489
00:26:26,733 --> 00:26:28,133
Why would I regret it?

490
00:26:28,267 --> 00:26:31,400
Ever since we separated,
I never felt free.

491
00:26:31,533 --> 00:26:33,200
Now, I finally have
peace of mind.

492
00:26:33,333 --> 00:26:34,400
[THEA GRUMBLES]

493
00:26:34,533 --> 00:26:35,833
You think
you're something special!

494
00:26:35,967 --> 00:26:40,300
Look, Thea. You're just trash
and worthless to Edward.

495
00:26:40,433 --> 00:26:42,900
But to me, you're useful.

496
00:26:43,067 --> 00:26:44,400
So if you change your mind

497
00:26:44,533 --> 00:26:46,500
and if you want to get even
with your husband

498
00:26:46,633 --> 00:26:49,300
for taking everything from you,
give me a call.

499
00:26:52,433 --> 00:26:57,433
Regina, give me one more chance
to rebuild our family.

500
00:26:57,567 --> 00:26:59,833
Please come back home.

501
00:26:59,967 --> 00:27:01,933
[SOBBING]

502
00:27:05,500 --> 00:27:07,733
I won't allow Regina
to be happy.

503
00:27:07,867 --> 00:27:09,267
Brace yourself, Regina.

504
00:27:09,400 --> 00:27:11,500
I'm not done with you yet.

505
00:27:11,633 --> 00:27:14,133
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]
